tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE website_traffic_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    page_visited VARCHAR(255),
    traffic_source VARCHAR(255),
    conversion_status BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE website_traffic_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    visitor_id INT,
    page_visited VARCHAR(255),
    referral_source VARCHAR(255),
    conversion_status BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE marketing_strategies (
    strategy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(255),
    target_audience VARCHAR(255),
    conversion_rate FLOAT,
    cost_per_conversion DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE website_traffic_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    page_url TEXT,
    visit_date DATE,
    source_channel TEXT,
    visit_duration INT
);

CREATE TABLE conversion_rates (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    page_url TEXT,
    conversion_date DATE,
    conversion_value DECIMAL,
    conversion_type TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE marketing_strategies (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name TEXT,
    strategy_description TEXT,
    target_audience TEXT,
    effectiveness_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE website_traffic_data (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    page_id INT,
    country VARCHAR,
    traffic_source VARCHAR
);

CREATE TABLE marketing_campaigns (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_name VARCHAR,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    budget DECIMAL,
    target_audience VARCHAR
);

CREATE TABLE user_engagement (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    page_id INT,
    duration_minutes INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR
);

CREATE TABLE website_visits (
    visit_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    visitor_id INT,
    visit_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    landing_page_id INT,
    referrer_page_id INT,
    conversion BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE page_traffic (
    page_id INT,
    visit_id INT,
    traffic_source VARCHAR(255),
    page_views INT,
    bounce_rate FLOAT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_page_id FOREIGN KEY (page_id) REFERENCES page_views(page_id),
    CONSTRAINT fk_visit_id FOREIGN KEY (visit_id) REFERENCES website_visits(visit_id)
);
